# Flight scanner

_ _ _

This is a Java application designed to track prices of a flight watchlist and send notifications about any changes to a Discord channel.

## Dependencies

- - -
The application uses the following dependencies:

Spring Boot: A framework for building Java applications.
Spring Boot Actuator: Provides endpoints for monitoring and managing the application.
Spring Data JPA: Simplifies the interaction with the database.
Spring Web: Enables building web applications using Spring MVC.
Spring Boot DevTools: Provides additional development-time features for increased productivity.
H2 Database: An in-memory database for development and testing purposes.
Log4j: A logging framework for Java applications.
Lombok: A library for reducing boilerplate code in Java classes.

//didn't implemented yet
JUnit: A unit testing framework for Java.

//didn't implemented yet
Discord4j: A library for interacting with the Discord API.

//soon, many API issues
Apache HttpClient: A library for making HTTP requests.
OkHttp: A library for making HTTP requests.

### Prerequisites
    To run the application, you need to have the following software installed:

    Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 or higher
    Apache Maven
